member.summary: Instance based class to write log messages based on a given configuration. Messages are routed based on category.

remarks.para: The LogWriter works as an entry point to the trace listeners. It will trace the through the s associated with the s for all the matching categories in the elements of the property of the log entry. If the "all events" special log source is configured, the log entry will be traced through the log source regardless of other categories that might have matched. If the "all events" special log source is not configured and the "unprocessed categories" special log source is configured, and the category specified in the logEntry being logged is not defined, then the logEntry will be logged to the "unprocessed categories" special log source. If both the "all events" and "unprocessed categories" special log sources are not configured and the property LogWarningsWhenNoCategoriesMatch is set to true, then the logEntry is logged to the "logging errors and warnings" special log source.
